  "reasoning": "The quantification clearly demonstrates that the 'True Cost of Not Knowing' in regulatory compliance for Life Sciences companies is substantial, ranging from $1.65M to over $29M annually in direct and indirect expenses. The Tier II (Velocity) SaaS pricing of ~$500-2000/month (avg. $1250/month or $15,000/year) is negligible compared to these costs. Even conservatively estimating a 10% reduction in manual time waste (from an average of $420,000/year), the software generates $42,000 in annual savings, resulting in a 2.8x ROI and breaking even in less than a working week. This calculation does not even fully account for the much larger, catastrophic costs of regulatory penalties ($10M+ per event) and delayed product launches ($5M-$50M+ per event), which the software significantly mitigates. The investment in proactive compliance is a direct hedge against these multi-million dollar risks, making the software a critical business asset rather than an overhead."
